Main article: [Fencing at the 2015 Pan American Games](/Fencing_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games)

The path to glory, or at least to participation, in [Fencing](/Fencing_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games) at the [2015 Pan American Games](/2015_Pan_American_Games) was, predictably, a convoluted affair. Athletes and nations alike had to navigate a stringent qualification system to earn their coveted spots in [Toronto](/Toronto), Canada. This wasn't merely about showing up; it was about proving worth, a process designed to filter the merely good from those deemed worthy of the Pan American stage.

The various competitive disciplines, each demanding its unique blend of precision, power, and psychological fortitude, were meticulously categorized for both individual and team contention.

**Individual Events:**
*   [Épée men](/Fencing_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games_%E2%80%93_Men%27s_%C3%A9p%C3%A9e)
*   [Épée women](/Fencing_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games_%E2%80%93_Women%27s_%C3%A9p%C3%A9e)
*   [Foil men](/Fencing_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games_%E2%80%93_Men%27s_foil)
*   [Foil women](/Fencing_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games_%E2%80%93_Women%27s_foil)
*   [Sabre men](/Fencing_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games_%E2%80%93_Men%27s_sabre)
*   [Sabre women](/Fencing_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games_%E2%80%93_Women%27s_sabre)

**Team Events:**
*   [Team épée men](/Fencing_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games_%E2%80%93_Men%27s_team_%C3%A9p%C3%A9e)
*   [Team épée women](/Fencing_at_the_2015_Pan_American_Games_%E2%80%93_Women%27s_team_%C3%A9p%C3%A9e)
